<subSubSection id="81B6651AFFE1FFE74D81FD79FBED9051" pageId="6" pageNumber="586" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C9133691FFE1FFE74D81FD79FBED9051" blockId="6.[151,1437,258,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="FBD8EA83FFE1FFE74D81FD79FEEE91AD" bold="true" box="[199,317,690,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Remarks:</emphasis>
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="0EAC4D12FFE1FFE74FCFFD78FC2891AD" authority="Morrison, 1973" authorityName="Morrison" authorityYear="1973" box="[649,1019,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thailandensis">
<emphasis id="FBD8EA83FFE1FFE74FCFFD78FC9091AD" box="[649,835,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">H. thailandensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AD3D4B60FFE1FFE74E0DFD79FC2891AD" box="[843,1019,690,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586" refId="ref4219" refString="SMorrison, W. P. (1973) A revision of the Hecalinae (HomoPtera) of the Oriental Region. Pacific Insects, 15 (3 &amp; 4), 379 - 438." type="journal article">Morrison, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by its genitalia but differs in having the following characters: subequal and truncate aedeagal processes with no subapical spine; aedeagal shaft slightly constricted laterally just above median length; one aedeagal process smooth and the other one serrated dorsally; pygofer lobe subacute apically; subgenital plate with spine starts from basal region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="81B6651AFFE1FFE74D81FC89FBF0903C" box="[199,1059,834,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C9133691FFE1FFE74D81FC89FBF0903C" blockId="6.[151,1437,258,859]" box="[199,1059,834,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="FBD8EA83FFE1FFE74D81FC89FE82903D" bold="true" box="[199,337,834,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Etymology:</emphasis>
The term “ 
<taxonomicName id="0EAC4D12FFE1FFE74C89FC89FDC9903D" authorityName="Naveed &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[463,538,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="snipus">snipus</taxonomicName>
” refers to the non-pointed aedeagal processes.
</paragraph>
